				<h3>SIDE EVENT BY SisVentures:<br><span class="small">Legal Design and Sustainable Development Goals</span></h3>
                                <img src="images/logos/logo_sisventures.jpg">
                                <div class="justify-left">
                                        <p>The 2030 Agenda for Sustainable Development was adopted at the United Nations in 2015. The 17 Sustainable Development Goals (SDGs) comprising the Agenda give the international community a shared blueprint for peace and prosperity. Over 90% of these goals and targets correspond with international human rights obligations. Yet legal design hasn’t been used as a tool for attaining them.</p>
					<p>Sis Ventures is a social impact start-up working to empower immigrant women. We have a unique, person-first approach to entrepreneurship incubating. We use legal design and legal tech to overcome the biggest obstacle immigrant women report on becoming an entrepreneur: access to legal information and advice needed to start and run a business.</p>
					<p>The international community has 11 years left to reach the Sustainable Development Goals. Some great progress has been made but we need to pick up the pace.</p>
					<p>Please join us in a cocktail event the night before Legal Design Summit to learn more about Sis Ventures’ work and to further explore how legal design and legal tech could be used to advance the Agenda 2030.</p>
					<p>The venue, Kunsthalle Helsinki, is a neo-classicist architectural gem often cited as the most elegant exhibition space in Helsinki.  Come and be inspired with us!</p>
                                        <p><strong>DATE AND TIME:</strong> Thursday 12.9.2019 at 19:00 - 21:00</p>
                                        <p><strong>LOCATION:</strong> <a href="https://www.google.com/maps/embed?pb=!1m18!1m12!1m3!1d1984.5211563772039!2d24.92914965194582!3d60.172105681873134!2m3!1f0!2f0!3f0!3m2!1i1024!2i768!4f13.1!3m3!1m2!1s0x46920a330621a21b%3A0x357551754892d31c!2sKunsthalle+Helsinki!5e0!3m2!1sen!2sfi!4v1565639700958!5m2!1sen!2sfi" class="lightbox">Kunsthalle Helsinki (Taidehalli), Nervanderinkatu 3</a></p>
